DisabledTests.TLS-ECH-Client-GREASEExtensions: We don't support ECH GREASE because we don't fallback to plaintext
DisabledTests.TLS-ECH-Client-GREASE-NoOverrideName: We don't support ECH GREASE because we don't fallback to plaintext

DisabledTests.TLS-ECH-Client-NoSupportedConfigs: We don't support fallback to cleartext when there are no valid ECH configs
DisabledTests.TLS-ECH-Client-SkipInvalidPublicName: We don't support fallback to cleartext when there are no valid ECH configs
DisabledTests.TLS-ECH-Server-EarlyData: Go does not support early (0-RTT) data
DisabledTests.TLS-ECH-Server-EarlyDataRejected: Go does not support early (0-RTT) data
DisabledTests.MLKEMKeyShareIncludedSecond: BoGo wants us to order the key shares based on its preference, but we don't support that
DisabledTests.MLKEMKeyShareIncludedThird: BoGo wants us to order the key shares based on its preference, but we don't support that
DisabledTests.PostQuantumNotEnabledByDefaultInClients: We do enable it by default!
DisabledTests.*-Kyber-TLS13: We don't support Kyber, only ML-KEM (BoGo bug ignoring AllCurves?)
DisabledTests.*-RSA_PKCS1_SHA256_LEGACY-TLS13: We don't support the legacy PKCS#1 v1.5 codepoint for TLS 1.3
DisabledTests.*-Verify-RSA_PKCS1_SHA256_LEGACY-TLS12: Likewise, we don't know how to handle it in TLS 1.2, so we send the wrong alert
DisabledTests.*-VerifyDefault-*: Our signature algorithms are not configurable, so there is no difference between default and supported
DisabledTests.NoCommonSignatureAlgorithms-TLS12-Fallba: We don't support the legacy RSA exchange (without tlsrsakex=1)
DisabledTests.*_SHA1-TLS12: We don't support SHA-1 in TLS 1.2 (without tlssha1=1)
DisabledTests.Agree-Digest-SHA1: We don't support SHA-1 in TLS 1.2 (without tlssha1=1)
DisabledTests.ServerAuth-SHA1-Fallback*: We don't support SHA-1 in TLS 1.2 (without tlssha1=1), so we fail if there are no signature_algorithms
DisabledTests.Agree-Digest-SHA256: We select signature algorithms in peer preference order. We should consider changing this.
DisabledTests.ECDSACurveMismatch-Verify-TLS13: We don't enforce the curve when verifying. This is a bug. We need to fix this.
DisabledTests.*-Verify-ECDSA_P224_SHA256-TLS13: Side effect of the bug above. BoGo sends a P-256 sigAlg with a P-224 key, and we allow it.
DisabledTests.TooManyKeyUpdates: crypto/tls doesn't implement spam protections (TODO: I think?)
DisabledTests.JustConfiguringKyberWorks: we always send a X25519 key share with Kyber
DisabledTests.KyberKeyShareIncludedSecond: we always send the Kyber key share first
DisabledTests.KyberKeyShareIncludedThird: we always send the Kyber key share first
DisabledTests.CurveID-Resume*: unexposed curveID is not stored in the ticket yet
